# Dashboard Component Guidelines

## Overview
The dashboard is the main landing page featuring widgets, statistics, and an Event Calendar using Syncfusion Schedule component.

## File Structure
- Component: [src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.html](mdc:src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.html)
- Styles: [src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.scss](mdc:src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.scss)
- Configuration: [angular.json](mdc:angular.json) - Syncfusion CSS imports

## Event Calendar Implementation

### Syncfusion Schedule Component
- Uses Syncfusion Schedule with Tailwind theme
- **NO custom styling** should be applied to the calendar itself
- Default Syncfusion styling provides proper contrast and readability
- Calendar is wrapped in a `.widget` container for consistent layout

### Widget Structure
```html
<div class="widget card">
  <div class="widget__header">
    <h3 class="widget__title">Event Calendar</h3>
    <div class="widget__legend">
      <!-- Legend items -->
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="widget__content">
    <!-- Syncfusion Schedule component -->
  </div>
</div>
```

## Layout Guidelines

### Grid System
- Main grid: 2fr 1fr (calendar + sidebar)
- Responsive: Single column on mobile
- Gap: 15px between grid items

### Widget Styling
- Header: Dark background (`#2d353c`) with white text
- Content: White background with padding
- Border radius: 6px
- Box shadow: Subtle elevation

## Best Practices

### 1. Event Calendar
- **DO NOT** apply custom CSS to Syncfusion Schedule
- Use wrapper styling for layout and positioning
- Let Syncfusion handle all calendar-specific styling

### 2. Widget Consistency
- All widgets follow the same header/content pattern
- Use consistent spacing and typography
- Maintain visual hierarchy

### 3. Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Stack widgets vertically on small screens
- Adjust grid layouts for different breakpoints

### 4. Performance
- Lazy load calendar data
- Use OnPush change detection where possible
- Optimize widget rendering

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Don't override Syncfusion Schedule styles
- Don't use `!important` on calendar elements
- Don't break the widget layout pattern
- Don't forget mobile responsiveness